bbcode_enabled = true
text = "Do you know why the USN colonised Meridia?

Why choose a random planet absurdly close to a gas giant?

When humanity first explored beyond the solar system, setting foot on other worlds, they picked up a signal.

Not any kind of normal signal, like a radio wave or laser, but a burst of supercharged radiation, the kind you would expect from a supernova or other interstellar phenomenon.

Only, it wasn't from any of those.

Evidently, the USN wasn't the only ones to discover the signal and come here.

That's how we're in this mess.




Anyway! Enough story time. 

I've set the teleport coordinates for the first excavation site I want you to explore, so just step into the teleporter behind you. 

I'll teleport you out of the site once you've explored it fully.



Oh, and remember to kill any aliens you see. 




<End Transmission. Teleport coordinates synthesised [0534, -0.3, 2043], Terminal activation = True>"
